INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Introducing NaplesQuailWest.com', 'introducing-naplesquailwest-com', 'In the heart of Naples, Florida, lies [Quail West](https://naplesquailwest.com), a community synonymous with luxury, elegance, and the serene lifestyle that Naples is famed for. This prestigious area, known for its sprawling estates, world-class golf courses, and exclusive amenities, has always been a beacon for discerning homeowners and real estate connoisseurs. Recognizing the unique allure of Quail West, the [Brehna Hovland team](http://hovlandrealty.com/), in partnership with Olympia Marketing, has launched a dedicated microsite to cater to their specific needs, and desire to become known as the exclusive brokerage for those searching for [Quail West Homes for Sale](https://naplesquailwest.com). This initiative is not just about showcasing properties; it’s about creating a platform that embodies the spirit of Quail West and elevates the real estate experience to new heights.

#### The Essence of Quail West

*Before delving into the specifics of the microsite and everything Olympia Marketing is doing for the Hovland Realty team, it is essential to understand what makes Quail West a pinnacle of luxury living. *

Nestled within lush landscapes and bordered by the pristine natural beauty of Southwest Florida, Quail West boasts over 1,180 acres of real estate, two 18-hole championship golf courses designed by Arthur Hills, and a newly renovated 70,000-square-foot clubhouse that offers fine dining, a spa, and wellness center, and a vibrant social atmosphere. The homes in Quail West are more than just structures; they are masterpieces of architectural finesse, ranging from expansive single-family homes to custom estate residences, each offering privacy, comfort, and opulence. Quail West is truly one of the top communities in all of Southwest Florida and Naples in particular (which is one of the jewels of Florida - on par with the highest luxury estates found in Miami, Fort Lauderdale, and other area throughout Florida). 

#### A Closer Look at the Microsite

The new microsite for Quail West, accessible at [https://naplesquailwest.com/](https://naplesquailwest.com/), is a result of meticulous planning and tailored marketing strategies designed by Olympia Marketing with the vision of the Brehna Hovland team. This site is a central hub for all things Quail West, providing current and prospective residents with detailed information about the community, listings, amenities, and the luxurious Naples lifestyle.

Full Site Design

Understanding that the first interaction many potential buyers have with Quail West is online, Olympia Marketing crafted a site that is both visually appealing and highly functional. The design reflects the luxury and exclusivity of the community, with a clean, elegant layout that emphasizes high-quality imagery and seamless navigation. Each page is structured to enhance user experience, ensuring that visitors can easily find comprehensive information about real estate options, community news, and lifestyle features.

Search Engine Optimization (SEO)

To reach a broader audience and connect with potential buyers who are searching for luxury homes in Naples, robust SEO strategies were implemented. The microsite is optimized for keywords related to Quail West and luxury living in Naples, enhancing its visibility and ranking on search engines. This strategic SEO not only attracts more traffic to the site but also ensures that the microsite reaches individuals who are specifically interested in high-end properties in Naples.

Pay-Per-Click (PPC) Marketing

Complementing the organic reach achieved through SEO, a targeted PPC campaign is actively managed to capture the attention of potential buyers. These ads are crafted to appear in search engine results and on various digital platforms where prospective buyers might spend their time. The focus is on reaching high-net-worth individuals looking for luxury real estate in Naples, thereby increasing the quality of leads and potential sales.

Supporting the Hovland Team

The ultimate goal of this microsite, aside from promoting Quail West, is to establish the Brehna Hovland team as the top real estate agents for this community. By providing a dedicated platform, Olympia Marketing has positioned the Hovland team as experts in Quail West, enhancing their reputation and authority in the Naples real estate market. The comprehensive marketing support, including the full site design, SEO, and PPC efforts, equips the team to serve their clients more effectively, offering a marketing synergy that is rare in real estate.

#### Conclusion

The new Quail West microsite is more than just a real estate website; it''s a strategic tool designed by Olympia Marketing to elevate the presence of the Brehna Hovland team in Naples'' competitive luxury real estate market. By focusing on a tailored approach that combines aesthetic appeal with functional design and advanced marketing strategies, the site aims to not only attract potential buyers but also provide them with a portal into the lifestyle that Quail West offers. Through this initiative, the Hovland team is set to become synonymous with luxury real estate in Naples, offering unmatched service to their clients and leading the market in one of Florida''s most exclusive communities.', '', NULL, 'NaplesQuailWest.com: Discover Naples Properties Today', 'NaplesQuailWest.com: Find your Naples dream home! Explore premium property listings and discover your perfect match today.', '', '2024-05-01 16:44:44', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Selling a Home Fast with Cobia Holdings', 'selling-a-home-fast-with-cobia-holdings', 'We''re excited to announce the onboarding of a new client Cobia Holdings. What is Cobia? Cobia is a real estate investor in Southwest Florida that specializes in helping people who are looking to [sell their house fast in Fort Myers](https://cobiaholdings.com) (and the rest of the surrounding Southwest Florida area) liquidate or sell their home quickly. 

Cobia has come to Olympia looking for help with their digital marketing and overall marketing services. We''re excited to be working with them and will be documenting our Journey over the coming months and years. 

## **Cobia Holdings - A Local Real Estate Investment Company**

I had some friends and family recently that were going through some tough times. Most people don''t realize that many homes in the real estate market are actually not viable for the open market. What do I mean? Well, in order to sell on the open/conventional RE market - you have to understand that most homes are going to need to be in prime shape. In the industry it''s called "turn-key ready." Because of this, most homeowners are going to spend around 5% of the home''s value prepping it for sale (in part because the better it shows, the more money they can sell it for). 

Unfortunately, many homes are occupied or owned by people that are: 

- Out of town

- Have health condition precluding rennovations

- Don''t have the money to rennovate

Because of this they won''t ever be able to sell their home on the open market (because investors aren''t there, and your average home buyer is looking to avoid a headache - not enter in one). 

So real estate firms like Cobia come along and either invest in the home directly, partnering with the home owner on fixing things up and helping to facilitate a sale (taking a profit margin), they buy the home out right and fix it up for the open market, or they connect homeowners with investors who would be willing to take on the home. 

In the scenario that plagued my friend, unfortunately an elderly parent had been occupying their home for years but hadn''t maintained the home. It needed a hundred thousand+ dollars worth of renovations in order to sell in a conventional way. Cobia came along and within a week took care of the owner, his son, purchasing the house for resale. They were happy as the property had grown precipitously since they purchased it in the late 90s. 

We look forward to helping others in the Southwest Florida community connect with this 100% local company, helping to keep the profit generated through these kinds of activities in the local community through various marketing and advertising efforts over the coming years.', '', NULL, 'Sell Your Home Fast: Expert Tips from Cobia Holdings in 2025', 'Discover expert tips from Cobia Holdings on selling your home fast. Get the best value for your property and expedite the selling process.', '', '2024-05-08 20:22:38', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Digital Dominance in Local Search for Outdoor Storage Facility: Client Success', 'digital-dominance-in-local-search-for-outdoor-storage-facility-client-success', 'As a digital-first marketing agency based in Southwest Florida, our focus has always been on harnessing the transformative power of the internet to boost our clients'' visibility and growth - it''s certainly not all we do, but in over 20 years, we''ve gotten exceedingly good at it...

Recently, we had the pleasure of collaborating with Frogpad Storage, a storage facility based in Englewood, their parent company - Blue Waters Development Group is in Cape Coral. We have big plans collectively, but engaged Olympia in a couple dimensions: 

Brought us in during the purchase of the business phase - to help them understand and evaluate the value of the digital assets the business was selling. This involved online assesments of the website, traffic, potential business opportunity (IE market size) as well as strategy on final implementation. 

- Initial simple website setup. 

- Initial SEO

- AdWords & Digital Marketing Deployment

- Redevelopment of the website

This engagement was particularly exciting due to its strategic importance and the digital pivots we worked through along the way - ultimately coming out the other end with a profitable and very scalable business that will most likely be expanding nationwide.

### Client Background

Frogpad Storage, through the patronage of it''s parent real estate development firm in Cape Coral, took over an existing facility in Englewood, aiming to revamp and dominate the local storage market. Initially constrained by budget post-acquisition, the client opted for a basic GoDaddy website to maintain their online presence without significant investment. This temporary solution was soon outstripped by their growing needs.

### Our Approach

Understanding the importance of a robust digital footprint, Olympia Marketing was tasked to elevate Frogpad Storage’s online presence from the ground up. We began by enhancing their initial website, allowing them to rank for nearly every relevant keyword in their niche, achieving top results not only in organic searches but also in local search rankings.

#### SEO Optimization

Our first move was a comprehensive SEO overhaul. The results were immediate and profound, catapulting Frogpad Storage to the forefront of search results in categories such as outdoor, boat, RV, trailer, and equipment storage.

#### Leveraging AdWords

Recognizing the competitive digital ad space, we implemented a targeted AdWords strategy. This significantly amplified their traffic, drawing hundreds more potential customers to their site each month, effectively tripling their online engagement.

### Challenges and Innovations

The digital space is fiercely competitive, often dominated by large, well-funded companies. Despite these challenges, our strategies not only carved out a significant digital presence for Frogpad Storage but also ensured they remained top-ranked amidst heavy competition.

### The Result

The culmination of our efforts was the launch of a new, optimized website that not only enhanced Frogpad Storage''s aesthetic appeal and user experience but also incorporated advanced tracking and analytics to better understand customer interactions and conversions.

At Olympia Marketing, we pride ourselves on fast, effective, and comprehensive digital marketing solutions tailored to meet and exceed our clients’ expectations. Frogpad Storage’s story is a testament to our commitment to excellence and our ability to navigate and dominate the digital marketing landscape, even for niche markets.

For more insights into how we can help your business thrive online, feel free to contact me directly at zach@olympiamarketing.com, and don’t forget to subscribe for more updates and expert tips from our team.

**For a full in-depth analysis I encourage you to watch the video I created about the project along with the launch of the new website: **

https://youtu.be/axQm7rMLveU', '', 'https://olympiamarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Untitled-4-1024x449.jpg', 'Olympia Marketing: Local Search Domination for Storage', 'Boost your outdoor storage facility''s local search with Olympia Marketing. Learn from our client success story and gain a competitive edge.', '', '2024-05-11 03:03:25', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('2024 Massive Leak - Google''s Search Secrets Revealed: What You Need to Know', '2024-massive-leak-googles-search-secrets-revealed-what-you-need-to-know', 'For years search engine optimizers and digital marketers have long speculated what''s happening behind the scenes and what the tech and algorithms are doing behind closed doors at Google. If you know the space - or if you don''t - you know that entities like Moz, SEMRush and hundreds of others have worked diligently to survey experts, run tests, compare notes, and compiled "what experts generally believe and see leads to results" - EVERY. SINGLE. YEAR. 

***This has been going on for over 20 years! ***

I remember reading Matt Cutts'' blog trying to gleen any information I could. Ironically, it''s mostly been for nothing - as TO THIS DAY - the basics still dominate. But, one exciting thing that happened this month was that Google accidentally published all of it''s secrets in the form of a 14,000+ page document that outlined EXACTLY how it does what it does. Here is a quick synopis of everything - and Olympia Marketing''s take away...

## The Big Google Leak

On March 13, thousands of internal Google documents were released on GitHub by an automated bot called yoshi-code-bot. These documents, from Google''s internal Content API Warehouse, were shared with Rand Fishkin, SparkToro co-founder. Michael King, CEO of iPullRank, also reviewed these documents and will provide further insights for Search Engine Land soon

## Why This Matters

These documents offer a rare glimpse into Google''s ranking algorithms, an invaluable resource for SEOs - but also allows us to see if they''ve been telling the truth all of these years with what they''ve revealed. And, it allows us to see how accurately many of our predictions have been from those "in the industry".

Turns out we were right about a lot - Google lies about virtually everything, but there are some suprising revelations. This leak is set to be one of the most significant events in the history of SEO, similar to the Yandex Search ranking factors leak in 2023.

***Key Direct Takeaways from the Documents***

- The information is up-to-date from March 2024.

- Ranking Features: The API documentation includes 2,596 modules and 14,014 attributes.

- Weighting: The documents **do not specify how ranking features are weighted**.

- Twiddlers: These functions adjust the ranking of a document based on various factors.

- Demotions: Content can be downgraded for reasons like mismatched links, user dissatisfaction, product reviews, location, and exact match domains.

- Change History: Google keeps a record of every version of every page it has indexed but only uses the last 20 changes for link analysis.

- Links Matter: Link diversity and relevance are crucial, and PageRank is still a significant factor.

- Successful Clicks Matter: High-quality content and user experience are essential for good rankings.

- Content Scores: Longer documents may be truncated, while shorter content is scored on originality.

- Your Money Your Life (YMYL) content gets special attention.

Thanks to [Search Engine Land](https://searchengineland.com/google-search-document-leak-ranking-442617) for gathering their Insights from the Experts: 

**Michael King:**
*To rank well, you need to drive successful clicks across a variety of queries and earn diverse links. This strategy indicates to Google that your content is valuable and deserving of a high ranking.*

**Rand Fishkin** (human garbage can and leftist idiot - who hasn''t worked in SEO for a long time but is still respected in digital marketing circles):
*Building a strong brand is more important than ever. A notable, well-recognized brand can significantly improve your organic search rankings and traffic.*

**Additional Important Findings**

- Entities and Authorship: Google tracks author information and uses it in ranking.

- SiteAuthority: Google uses a metric called "siteAuthority" to evaluate sites.

- Chrome Data: Google uses data from the Chrome browser for ranking.

- Whitelists: Google has whitelists for certain domains, particularly related to elections and COVID.

- Small Sites: Google may boost or demote small personal sites or blogs using specific features.

- Freshness and Relevance

- Google considers dates in the byline, URL, and on-page content for freshness.

- Google compares page embeddings to determine if a document is a core topic of the website.

- Domain registration information is also stored and used.

- Page Titles and Fonts

- Page titles are important, and Google has a metric to measure their relevance.

- Google measures the average weighted font size of terms in documents and anchor text.

## Olympia Marketing''s Thoughts

There''s not really too much crazy here although these are the things that stand out the most: 

**Tons of Factors Determine Ranking** - The astounding number of factors that Google is using to rank things - if you tally up the modules and attributes you''re just under 20,000 different factors. Most businesses don''t understand this. Luckily if you get the basics correct you don''t need much else. 

**Demotion of Keyword Match Domains is Nonsense **- Even though this document says they do sometimes demote keyword match domains (and I''ve seen this with clearly bogus domains with lots of dashes) it''s been my experience having done this 100+ times that keyword match domains do phenomenally well. More lying from Google even in their leaks? 4D chess perhaps...

**Your Web Design Matters** - Click tracking - it''s always been thought Google DOES include on-site behavior in determining ranking, even though Google has adamantly denied this, we now know they were lying and do - in fact - use this as a metric in weighing websites (and for good reason). So tweaking your UI to make it easier, more helpful, etc. DOES have an impact not just on general conversion rates, but also on how many people will eventually see your stuff (by way of it''s impact on SEO). 

**Chrome** - Chrome being used to mine data on sites for ranking purposes is interesting, although not surprising. I can already see some ways this could be gamed over time potentially. 

**Newer Content Helps **- Having fresh content with the date of publishing clearly marked is helpful. I''ve debated this for sometime, but it seems pretty clear (unless this leak is to throw people off completely) that newer fresher content does actually help and it''s certainly something I''ve seen in my recent tests. 

**Privacy & Author Reputation** - Domain Registration information being stored, along with the tracking of personal blogs, as well the saving of all of copies of a website (something I''ll get back to in a second) as well as authors effectively having a "profile" as far as Google search is interesting, but concerning. Basically this could be a privacy nightmare overall. Google could know, behind the scenes for example based on non-public ICANN data who owns websites and then demote them. 

A couple thoughts on the above... I know directly of a case that was settled out of court with a prominent person in the SEO world - who was personally attacked by Google - although one site was in violation of some of Google''s policies, they decided to go after ALL sites owned or operated by this person regardless of circumstance, topic, or legal precedent (IE these could have been owned, held, or operated by whole separate businesses - just their ASSOCIATION with this person caused them to be attacked and removed from Google''s SERPs). 

Google storing old copies of websites is interesting - and aligns sort of (but is also at odds with) something we''ve noticed for sometime... starting about 18 months ago (back in late 2022 early 2023) Google seemed to simply stop indexing pages. At first I believed this was an anomaly with the site I was seeing this on, but after running tests on multiple new sites - I noticed the same thing over and over - Google simply wasn''t crawling and indexing sites. In fact, to this day - and with a client I''ll be doing a highlight on here shortly - only if you FORCE GOOGLE''S CRAWLERS - via indexing tools like [Tag Parrot ](https://tagparrot.com?via=t4zkw51royv19tlpuiv3)(which manually submits your full site via your Search Central and your sitemap). The client in question has been adding to their website nonstop for a half decade but only about 20 pages were indexed. By setting up manual submissions we were able to get them all 700+ pages indexed, and exploded their views and impressions to over 100,000/month (and now they''re top ranked nationally in their discipline). 

**Google is the World''s Ministry of Information**

Additionally the fact that Google has "authority" sites for elections and COVID is also terrible but not unexpected. Google is the world''s defacto "ministry of information" controlling much of the information one can connect to, see or find and controls such a massive percent of both the onramps to content as well as the content itself (via YouTube which is the #2 search engine on the planet). We also know, as Google publicly came out shortly after the supposed "covid outbreak" that YouTube would be heavily censoring any and all information not deemed "mainstream/approved." 

So to close things out, although some interesting things have come to light - it''s nothing that crazy or that surprising, although it finallly confirms that Google has been bold-faced lying for decades even to it''s closest "allies" in the digital marketing community - which really does bring into question their original slogan... "do no evil" and one has to ask... why would I trust an organization that''s now been associated with so much fraud on the advertising level, and the lying to the public and SEO level with being the gatekeeper of information globally?', '', NULL, 'Google SEO in 2025: Olympia Marketing''s Search Secrets', 'Olympia Marketing reveals Google''s search secrets! Boost your online presence in 2025 with proven SEO strategies.', '', '2024-05-31 20:52:13', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Fort Myers Lawn & Paver Company - TLS Lawn Service & TLS Pavers Client Success Story', 'fort-myers-lawn-paver-company-tls-lawn-service-tls-pavers-client-success-story', 'Recently longtime friend and client''s Reyna & Juan who run the [Fort Myers Lawn Service and Tree Removal Company](https://tlslawnservice.com) - TLS Lawn Service came to us and asked - in addition to what we had already provided them (previously we had optimized their website on Wix) what we could to do help increase business even more, and help them with their new business. TLS Lawn & Service has existed in Fort Myers for many years serving clients throughout Southwest Florida and Lee County with all of their lawn service needs including: 

- Tree Trimming & Tree Removal

- Sod & Plant Installation

- Mulch & Landscaping

So we discussed the current situation (previously hosted on wix) and that this would be the perfect time to upgrade as well as build out a brand new site using one of our customizable themes and put together a plan and executed. 

For TLS Pavers a [Fort Myers Paver company](https://tlspavers.com) that works on all kinds of paver projects including landscaping and pavers for pools and other decorative walk-spaces, we decided to build out a brand new custom site and similarly, execute under one major account - google adwords. 

### TLS Lawn Service: Fort Myers Tree Service Excellence

#### A Comprehensive Approach to Lawn Care and Tree Services

TLS Lawn Service has established itself as a leader in lawn care and tree services in Fort Myers. Specializing in tree trimming, pruning, and comprehensive lawn maintenance, the company offers a full spectrum of services designed to enhance the beauty and health of residential and commercial landscapes.

#### The Power of a New Website

The journey began with the creation of a modern, user-friendly website. This site not only showcases the breadth of services offered by TLS Lawn Service but also includes optimized content tailored to the needs of local customers. By incorporating key phrases such as "Fort Myers Tree Service," the website was strategically designed to attract organic traffic from search engines.

#### Search Engine Optimization (SEO)

SEO was at the heart of the digital strategy for TLS Lawn Service. By conducting thorough keyword research, optimizing on-page elements, and creating high-quality content, the company significantly improved its search engine rankings. Meta descriptions, alt tags, and header tags were meticulously optimized to ensure that the website appeared prominently in search results for relevant queries.

#### Hosting Transition and Performance

A seamless hosting transition played a pivotal role in enhancing the website''s performance. Faster load times and improved site reliability not only contributed to a better user experience but also positively impacted search engine rankings. This technical upgrade ensured that visitors could access the site quickly and efficiently, reducing bounce rates and increasing engagement.

#### Pay-Per-Click (PPC) Advertising

To complement the organic traffic generated by SEO, a targeted PPC campaign was launched. This campaign focused on key services and geographic areas, ensuring that TLS Lawn Service reached potential customers actively seeking tree services in Fort Myers. The combination of compelling ad copy and strategic bidding resulted in a steady stream of qualified leads.

#### Remarkable Results

Since implementing these strategies, TLS Lawn Service has experienced a dramatic increase in search engine visibility. Rankings for key terms like "Fort Myers Tree Service" have improved by roughly 50% each month. This growth has translated into a significant uptick in website traffic, inquiries, and ultimately, business revenue.

### TLS Pavers: Fort Myers Pavers Expertise

#### Premier Paving Solutions

TLS Pavers offers top-tier paving services in Fort Myers, specializing in driveway and walkway installations. Their commitment to quality craftsmanship and customer satisfaction has earned them a stellar reputation in the local community.

#### A Fresh Digital Presence

Similar to TLS Lawn Service, TLS Pavers embarked on a digital transformation with a newly designed website. This platform highlights their extensive portfolio, service offerings, and customer testimonials, all while being optimized for search engines with a focus on "Fort Myers Pavers."

#### SEO Strategies for Success

The SEO strategy for TLS Pavers involved detailed keyword analysis to identify high-value search terms. On-page optimization, including the use of targeted keywords in titles, headers, and content, was crucial. Additionally, the creation of engaging blog posts and articles helped establish TLS Pavers as an authority in the paving industry.

#### Efficient Hosting and User Experience

Transitioning to a new hosting provider ensured that the TLS Pavers website operated smoothly and efficiently. Enhanced performance metrics, such as faster load times and reduced downtime, contributed to a better user experience and higher search engine rankings.

#### Strategic PPC Campaigns

PPC advertising was leveraged to reach customers actively searching for paving services in Fort Myers. By focusing on specific keywords and demographics, the PPC campaign drove targeted traffic to the website, resulting in increased inquiries and bookings.

#### Impressive Outcomes

The results for TLS Pavers have been equally impressive, with search engine rankings improving significantly month over month. The company''s visibility for key terms like "Fort Myers Pavers" has surged, leading to a notable increase in website visits and customer engagement. This upward trend in digital presence has directly contributed to business growth and profitability.

### Conclusion

The success stories of TLS Lawn Service and TLS Pavers illustrate the transformative power of effective digital marketing strategies. By investing in a robust online presence through SEO, hosting transitions, and PPC campaigns, both companies have achieved remarkable growth and established themselves as leaders in their respective fields. Their experiences underscore the importance of a well-rounded digital strategy in today''s competitive business landscape.

For businesses looking to enhance their online presence and achieve similar success, the journeys of TLS Lawn Service and TLS Pavers serve as a blueprint. With the right approach and dedication, any business can leverage the power of digital marketing to reach new heights.', '', 'https://olympiamarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Screenshot-2024-06-17-at-8.54.31 PM-1024x571.png', 'TLS Lawn & Pavers: Fort Myers Success Story', 'TLS Lawn & Pavers: Fort Myers success story! Discover how our lawn and paver services achieve outstanding results for our clients.', '', '2024-06-18 00:59:16', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('The Best Esthetician Websites', 'the-best-esthetician-websites', 'At Olympia we''ve been marketing and advertising businesses of all sizes for the last 20 years. Back when we started a website was seen as a luxury, these days it''s an absolute MUST! - in fact the only other thing we consider as much of a necessity these days as a website day 1 - is a google my business page. It''s become that important. More important than email, a business card, etc. 

As we''ve dove deep into the Esthetician, Spa, Salon and other beauty industries over the last two years - adding a number of clients in the space, including award winning [Esthetician School Skincare Academy of Florida](https://skincareacademyflorida.com/) as well as the amazing [Naples Luxury Salon, Salon Rejuvenation](https://salonrejuvenation.com/) and finally [Nova Beauty](https://www.novabeautyco.net/) (a Medspa and Facial Spa in Bartonville TX) - we''ve realized there''s very little information on industry-specific websites and just what needs to be included. 

Before we review some sites, let''s talk about what makes a great website. 

## What Makes the Best Esthetician Websites?

In the digital age, an esthetician’s website is more than just an online presence; it is a vital tool for attracting and retaining clients, a sales person that helps you sell, it''s the inside of your space that communicates your personality and your businesses unique offerings - it''s truly a tool that should be working for 24/7, 365. Whether you run a spa, salon, beauty clinic, esthetician business REALLY ANY BUSINESS in the beauty industry having a high-quality, well-converting website is essential for success. In this blog post, we will explore the key elements that make "***The Best Esthetician Websites***" stand out and convert visitors into loyal clients.

#### 1. **Stunning Visual Design**

Aesthetic appeal is crucial for any esthetician website... see what we did there ;). Just like a beautiful, clean, refreshed face makes a person more confident, and more likely to achieve their goals - a clean, modern, and visually appealing design not only captures visitors'' attention but also conveys the quality and professionalism of your services. 

High-resolution images of your salon, spa treatments, and before-and-after photos of clients can create a strong first impression.

***Key Rule: Your website should be easy to use, and at-a-glance (just a half second glance) people should understand your spa business'' offerings. ***

#### 2. **User-Friendly Navigation**

User experience (UX) is a critical factor in website performance, marketing, and ensuring your customers find what they''re looking for. The best esthetician websites feature simple, intuitive navigation, allowing visitors to find information quickly and easily. Clear menus, well-organized service pages, and easy-to-find contact information are essential elements.

***Key Rule: Don''t over complicate or use unique language when structuring menus and navigation. Just stick to conventions. Have services under a "services" section - and "products" under your products section. Everything should be at most 2 clicks from the homepage. ***

#### 3. **Mobile Responsiveness**

Particularly with local service based businesses mobile is not an option but an ABSOLUTE NECESSITY. In our experience approximately 70% of web traffic in the spa and beauty industry is coming from mobile devices. So, it is imperative that your website is mobile-friendly. A responsive design ensures that your site looks and functions well on all screen sizes, providing a seamless experience for users on smartphones and tablets.

***Key Rule: "Responsive" just means... "looks good on mobile." Make sure whatever service or company you retain keeps mobile in mind when developing your site. Make sure you test your own website on a few different kinds of mobile devices to see how attractive, easy to use, and intuitive it is. ***

#### 4. **Compelling Content**

High-quality content is key to engaging and informing your audience. Detailed descriptions of your services, informative blog posts about skincare and beauty tips, and client testimonials build trust and showcase your expertise. Additionally, using SEO best practices to optimize your content can help your website rank higher in search engine results.

***Key Rule: Most business owners I''ve talked with over the years struggle with this. You don''t have to. When you''re talking to your clients take note of everything they ask and everything you''re telling them. All of this is exactly what needs to go on your website. ***

#### 5. **Online Booking System**

Time is money, and you wnat to make things as simple as possible for your clients right... RIGHT? So, why not save your clients a step, a phone call, etc. and integrate your existing booking system (if the option is available - or consider a tool that DOES allow online booking). An integrated online booking system allows potential clients to schedule appointments directly through your website. This feature not only enhances user experience but also reduces the administrative burden on your staff.

#### 6. **Clear Calls to Action (CTAs)**

Effective CTAs guide visitors towards taking desired actions, such as booking an appointment, signing up for a newsletter, or contacting you for more information. The best esthetician websites use strategically placed and visually distinct CTAs to drive conversions.

***Key Point: If you don''t guide your users using language they''re much less likely to perform the actions you want (contact you, sign up for an appointment, inquire for more information). ***

#### 7. **Fast Loading Times**

Website speed is a critical factor in user satisfaction and SEO. A slow-loading website can frustrate visitors and increase bounce rates. Optimizing your site for speed by compressing images, leveraging browser caching, and using a reliable hosting service can significantly improve performance.

#### 8. **Testimonials and Reviews**

Client testimonials and reviews serve as powerful social proof. Featuring positive feedback from satisfied clients can build trust and credibility, encouraging new visitors to book your services.

#### 9. **Secure and Easy Payment Options**

Providing secure and convenient payment options is essential for customer satisfaction. Ensure that your website supports various payment methods and complies with security standards to protect clients'' sensitive information.

#### 10. **Regular Updates and Maintenance**

A well-maintained website reflects professionalism and reliability. Regularly updating your content, checking for broken links, and ensuring that all features work correctly can keep your website running smoothly and efficiently.

Keep these 10 things in mind and you''ll have a fantastic precense for your beauty industry business.', '', NULL, 'Best Esthetician Websites: Enhance Your Online Presence', 'Best esthetician websites: Olympia Marketing showcases designs to boost your online presence and attract clients effectively.', '', '2024-06-27 20:53:41', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Top 25 Marketing Tips for Builders & Developers', 'top-25-marketing-tips-for-builders-developers', 'In the highly competitive construction and real estate development industry, a robust marketing strategy can make all the difference in standing out from the competition and attracting clients. We get it... marketing your business is difficult. We''ve been helping builders & developers with marketing their services for over 20 years. As a builder or a developer you often have many different audiences to consider such as the following: 

- Board of Directors & Shareholders (or outside investment firms)

- The Community or City You''re Pitching Your Project

- Employee (internal marketing to keep your entire team on the same page and understanding your company vision and mission)

- An array of different customer personas, including various types of renters, end-buyers, or investment firms that you hope will purchase your project once completed

It can be a daunting task to manage all of this, but we''ve helped all kinds of builders & developers from the smallest start up single family home builder - to a multi-national, multi-billion dollar firm that has properties coast-to-coast including one of the largest master planned towns that has been under continuous development for the last decade+. We actually are SO good at what we do, the aforementioned client broke all of their records and goals in the first year alone - and this was AFTER switching from a "high-end" (read needlessly expensive) firm to our CEO''s plan and reduced their costs by over 90%. 

So, with this in mind, based on our existing expertise as well as the expertise of a number of resources and experts from around the web, we''ve scoured and compiled the top 25 marketing tips for builders and developers. 

## Let''s get to the top 25 marketing tips for builders & developers:

Here are the top 25 marketing tips for builders and developers to help you elevate your marketing game and build a successful brand presence. 

#### 1. Create a Compelling Website

Your website is the digital face of your business. Ensure it is visually appealing, easy to navigate, and mobile-friendly. Highlight your projects with detailed descriptions and use high-quality images and videos to showcase your work. A well-designed website can significantly enhance your online presence and attract potential clients​ ([Venveo](https://www.venveo.com/blog/marketing-to-builders-the-ultimate-guide))​​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 2. Leverage SEO

Search Engine Optimization (SEO) is essential for improving your website’s visibility on search engines. Use relevant keywords related to your industry and location to attract potential clients. Regularly update your website with fresh content to maintain high search rankings​ ([Bokka Group](https://www.bokkagroup.com/home-builder-insights/articles/boost-your-home-builder-marketing))​.

#### 3. Utilize Social Media

Actively engage on social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, and Twitter. Share updates about your projects, behind-the-scenes content, and industry news. Use these platforms to interact with your audience, answer queries, and build a community around your brand​ ([SmartTouch Interactive](https://smarttouchinteractive.com/newsblog/social-media-and-facebook-post-ideas-for-home-builders/))​​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 4. Invest in Quality Content

Content marketing is a powerful tool for builders and developers. Create blog posts, articles, and videos that provide valuable information to your audience. Topics can include home maintenance tips, the latest construction trends, and project updates. Quality content helps establish your authority in the industry and drives traffic to your website​ ([Venveo](https://www.venveo.com/blog/marketing-to-builders-the-ultimate-guide))​.

#### 5. Implement Email Marketing

Email marketing is an effective way to nurture leads and keep your audience informed about your projects. Send regular newsletters with updates, special offers, and industry news. Personalize your emails to make them more relevant to your recipients​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 6. Use High-Quality Visuals

High-quality images and videos can significantly enhance your marketing efforts. Invest in professional photography and videography to showcase your projects. Use these visuals on your website, social media, and marketing materials to create a strong impression​ ([Bokka Group](https://www.bokkagroup.com/home-builder-insights/articles/boost-your-home-builder-marketing))​​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 7. Host Open Houses and Events

Open houses and events are excellent opportunities to showcase your work and interact with potential clients. Organize tours of your completed projects, and invite real estate agents, potential buyers, and the media. Events create buzz and provide a platform for networking​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 8. Leverage Client Testimonials

Client testimonials are powerful social proof that can help build trust with potential clients. Collect and showcase testimonials from satisfied clients on your website and marketing materials. Video testimonials can be particularly impactful​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 9. Utilize Virtual Tours

Virtual tours allow potential clients to explore your projects from the comfort of their homes. Use 3D tours and interactive floor plans to provide an immersive experience. Virtual tours can help you reach a wider audience and generate more leads​ ([Bokka Group](https://www.bokkagroup.com/home-builder-insights/articles/boost-your-home-builder-marketing))​​ ([SmartTouch Interactive](https://smarttouchinteractive.com/newsblog/social-media-and-facebook-post-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 10. Implement PPC Advertising

Pay-Per-Click (PPC) advertising can help you reach potential clients quickly. Use Google Ads and social media advertising to target specific demographics and locations. Monitor your campaigns regularly to optimize performance and maximize ROI​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 11. Sponsor Local Events

Sponsoring local events and sports teams can increase your brand visibility and create a positive association with your community. Look for events that align with your brand values and target audience​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 12. Invest in Print Advertising

Despite the rise of digital marketing, print advertising still holds value. Advertise in local newspapers, magazines, and real estate publications to reach potential clients who prefer traditional media​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 13. Use Direct Mail

Direct mail campaigns can be an effective way to reach potential clients. Send brochures, postcards, and newsletters to targeted mailing lists. Include a clear call to action to encourage recipients to contact you​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 14. Optimize for Local SEO

Local SEO is crucial for builders and developers who want to attract clients in specific geographic areas. Optimize your website for local search terms, and create and verify your Google My Business listing to improve your visibility in local search results​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 15. Participate in Trade Shows

Trade shows provide excellent opportunities to network with industry professionals and potential clients. Set up an engaging booth, distribute marketing materials, and collect contact information from attendees. Follow up with leads after the event to nurture relationships​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 16. Develop Strategic Partnerships

Form partnerships with complementary businesses such as real estate agents, interior designers, and landscapers. These partnerships can lead to cross-promotion and referrals, helping you reach a broader audience​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 17. Create a Referral Program

Encourage satisfied clients to refer their friends and family by offering incentives such as discounts or gift cards. A referral program can help you generate new leads and build a loyal customer base​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 18. Showcase Employee Expertise

Highlight the expertise of your team members on your website and social media. Share their stories, accomplishments, and insights to humanize your brand and build trust with your audience​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 19. Utilize Video Marketing

Video marketing is a powerful way to engage your audience. Create videos that showcase your projects, provide construction tips, and share client testimonials. Post these videos on your website, social media, and YouTube​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([SmartTouch Interactive](https://smarttouchinteractive.com/newsblog/social-media-and-facebook-post-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 20. Focus on Customer Experience

Provide exceptional customer service to build strong relationships with your clients. Respond promptly to inquiries, address concerns, and go the extra mile to exceed client expectations. Happy clients are more likely to refer you to others and leave positive reviews​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 21. Implement Retargeting Campaigns

Retargeting campaigns can help you stay top-of-mind with potential clients who have visited your website. Use retargeting ads to remind them of your services and encourage them to return to your site and complete a desired action​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 22. Use Influencer Marketing

Partner with local influencers and bloggers to promote your projects. Influencers can help you reach a wider audience and add credibility to your brand. Choose influencers whose followers align with your target demographic​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 23. Leverage Data Analytics

Use data analytics to track the performance of your marketing campaigns. Analyze metrics such as website traffic, conversion rates, and social media engagement to identify what works and what needs improvement. Use this data to refine your marketing strategy​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

#### 24. Engage in Community Involvement

Get involved in your local community by sponsoring events, participating in charity work, and supporting local initiatives. Community involvement can enhance your brand’s reputation and create positive associations with your business​ ([Cedreo](https://cedreo.com/blog/construction-marketing-ideas/))​​ ([Chatter Buzz](https://www.chatterbuzzmedia.com/marketing-strategy-ideas-for-home-builders/))​.

#### 25. Develop a Strong Brand Identity

A strong brand identity sets you apart from your competitors. Develop a consistent brand image, including your logo, color scheme, and messaging. Ensure that all your marketing materials reflect your brand identity to create a cohesive and professional look​ ([Venveo](https://www.venveo.com/blog/marketing-to-builders-the-ultimate-guide))​​ ([Townsquare Interactive](https://townsquareinteractive.com/blog/home-builder-marketing-ideas/))​.

Implementing these "Top 25 Marketing Tips for Builders & Developers" can significantly enhance your marketing efforts and help you attract more clients. From creating a compelling website and leveraging SEO to utilizing social media and investing in quality content, these strategies will help you build a robust brand presence and drive business growth. Remember, the key to successful marketing is consistency, creativity, and a focus on providing value to your audience. Start incorporating these tips into your marketing plan today and watch your business thrive.', '', NULL, 'Marketing Tips for Builders: Improve Your Strategy', 'Marketing tips for builders: Olympia Marketing offers top strategies to boost your construction business. Improve your marketing and drive success in 2025.', '', '2024-07-02 19:20:07', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Esthetician Marketing Tips to Grow & Attract New Clients', 'esthetician-marketing-tips-to-grow-attract-new-clients', '**Think you know what it takes to market your skincare and esthetic business successfully? We''ve been marketing and advertising businesses of all kinds for over 2 decades. We''ve recently started working more and more in the beauty industry - including the skincare, esthetician and salon industries, helping companies of all sizes grow, expand, and the owners achieve their dreams. **

Learn from our passion, our successes and our mistakes** - prepare to be surprised by some of our most essential esthetician marketing strategies.**

Before we get to How to Market Your Esthetician Business Effectively let''s talk about some of our recent successes... we''ve helped a local esthetician school absolutely skyrocket above and beyond their competition. In less than 18 months, they''ve become one of the [hottest and fastest growing esthetician schools in South Florida](https://skincareacademyflorida.com). 

Another client is successfully growing her small [salon practice in Naples Florida](https://salonrejuvenation.com/). And finally, we''ve helped an [esthetician in the Dallas area (Bartonville precisely](https://www.novabeautyco.net/)) compete with entrenched businesses and provide an income for her family and become an inspiration to her daughter. Here''s what we typically look at with each project. 

## How to Market Your Esthetician Business Effectively

Marketing your skincare and esthetics business goes beyond mere promotion; it''s a vital link connecting your expertise to the clients who seek it. In an industry where personal touch and professional skill are paramount, effectively presenting and communicating your services is essential.

The journey of an esthetician in the digital age brings unique challenges. Attracting and retaining clients in a sea of competitors requires more than just skill in the treatment room; it demands savvy, creativity, and a keen understanding of the digital world.

Today, we delve into a multitude of the best marketing ideas for estheticians. Whether you''re an experienced esthetician or just starting out, these insights will set you on the right path to improve your marketing strategies and enhance your connection with your clientele. Let’s dive in!

## Best Social Media Platforms for Estheticians

Navigating the diverse landscape of social media is a crucial element of modern marketing for skincare and esthetic businesses. Each platform offers unique opportunities to connect with different audiences, and understanding how to leverage these differences is key to a successful strategy.

Our clear winners... Instagram and facebook. Instagram allows you to show off your amazing skills - both in the moment and before and after videos/images. Facebook although a little more cumbersome, has a tremendous amount of opportunity as most clients find THEIR CLIENTS are on Facebook (boomers with disposable income). 

### Leveraging Social Media Effectively

**Content Pillars:** Establish content pillars that resonate with your brand and audience. These could include educational content like skincare tips and recommendations, trust-building content like client testimonials, or a day in the life. Consistency in these pillars ensures your content remains focused and relevant.

**Content Creation:** Invest in creating high-quality, engaging content. This could range from educational posts to visually appealing before-and-after images. Your content should not only reflect your expertise but also capture your audience''s attention. If content creation isn''t your thing, consider using a content subscription for access to hundreds of educational and data-driven templates.

**Community Engagement:** Foster a sense of community by actively engaging with your audience. Respond to comments, participate in relevant conversations, and use these interactions to build a loyal following. This engagement is crucial for building trust and rapport with potential clients.

## How to Retain Clients as an Esthetician

Attracting clients is just the first step for skincare professionals and estheticians; the real challenge lies in keeping them engaged and loyal. Implementing effective client engagement and retention strategies can create an environment that clients want to return to and support your business.

### Key Strategies for Client Engagement and Retention

**Referral Programs:** Referral programs are a powerful tool for organic growth. Encourage your existing clients to refer friends and family by offering them incentives, like discounts on future services or special treatments. This not only brings in new clients but also reinforces the loyalty of current ones.

**Loyalty Rewards:** Implement a loyalty program to reward repeat clients. Whether it''s a point system, discounts on regular services, or exclusive access to new treatments, these rewards make clients feel valued and more likely to return.

**Personalized Communications:** Personalization is key in client communications. Tailor your emails, appointment reminders, and follow-ups to address clients by name and reference their specific interests or past treatments. This level of personal attention goes a long way in building strong relationships.

**Personalized Client Experiences:** Customize the client experience from the moment they step into your clinic. This can range from personalized treatment plans to remembering their preferences in skincare products or techniques. A personalized approach shows clients that they are not just another appointment in your schedule.

## Top Digital Marketing Tips for Estheticians

A robust online presence is indispensable for estheticians looking to grow their business. Digital marketing is not just about reaching a wider audience; it''s about strategically positioning your brand in the digital world.

### Essential Digital Marketing Strategies

**SEO:** Search Engine Optimization (SEO) is crucial for making your website more visible and accessible to potential clients. Utilize effective keywords, well-structured URLs, and ensure your site loads quickly to improve your rankings on search engines. This non-paid traffic can significantly increase your online visibility, drawing more clients in.

**Google Business Profile:** A well-optimized Google Business Profile can significantly boost your local search presence. It''s an invaluable tool for providing essential business information and capturing local clientele. Make sure your profile is complete with up-to-date contact information, a services list, and client reviews.

**Email Mailing List:** Building an email list allows for direct, personalized marketing communications. It''s a platform for keeping your clients informed about new services, special offers, and skincare tips, maintaining continuous engagement with your audience.

**Targeted Advertising:** Invest in targeted ads to reach specific demographics or interests. Platforms like Facebook and Google offer sophisticated targeting options, ensuring that your ads are seen by those most likely to be interested in what you have to offer.

## Creating Engaging Content for Esthetician Marketing

In the realm of skincare and esthetics, content marketing is not just about broadcasting information and showing off your client''s post-facial glow; it’s about engaging, educating, and connecting with your audience.

### Effective Content Marketing Tactics

**The Power of a Blog:** A blog is a fantastic platform for sharing your knowledge and expertise in skincare and esthetics. Well-crafted blog posts like “My Top Oil Cleanser Recommendations,” or “Diet and Lifestyle Factors to Avoid if You’re an Acne Sufferer” provide valuable information to your audience, establish your authority in the field, and improve your website''s SEO.

**Video Content:** Video content is increasingly crucial in digital marketing. Videos that demonstrate treatments, showcase product reviews, or offer quick skincare tips can be highly engaging. They help in not just telling but showing your audience the value of your services and the expertise behind them.

**Educational Content:** Educational content positions you as an industry expert and builds trust with your audience. Sharing insights about skincare routines, treatment processes, and the science behind beauty treatments can help demystify the process for clients and make them feel more informed and comfortable choosing your services.

## How to Build Your Brand Identity as an Esthetician

Establishing a strong brand identity is crucial for any esthetician seeking to stand out in a competitive market. Your brand identity is more than just a logo or a color scheme; it''s the essence of your values, your approach to skincare, and the experiences you offer.

### Key Elements of Brand Identity

**Visual Elements:** Your brand''s visual elements, like fonts, colors, and logo, should be consistent across all platforms and marketing materials. This consistency helps in creating a cohesive and professional image that clients will recognize and trust.

**Content Style & Tone of Voice:** The style and tone of your content play a significant role in how your brand is perceived. Whether it''s educational, inspirational, or conversational, ensure that it aligns with your brand''s personality and values. A distinct tone of voice helps build a unique brand persona that resonates with your audience.

**Imagery:** Invest in high-quality imagery that reflects the quality of your services. Professional photos of your team, treatments, products, and clinic set a standard for what clients can expect when they choose you.

**Alignment Across Online and Physical Branding:** Ensure that your branding is aligned both online and in your physical clinic. This alignment strengthens your brand''s identity and provides a seamless experience for clients, reinforcing your professionalism and attention to detail.

**Storytelling:** Incorporate storytelling into your branding strategy. Share your journey, your inspirations, and the passion behind your work. This personal touch can create an emotional connection with your audience, making your brand more relatable and engaging.

## Collecting and Utilizing Client Feedback

For estheticians, client feedback is essential for continual growth and improvement. Actively seeking and implementing feedback demonstrates a commitment to excellence and client satisfaction.

### Practical Ways to Collect and Act on Client Feedback

**Surveys and Questionnaires:** Encourage clients to share their thoughts through surveys and questionnaires. These can be conducted post-treatment or via email, focusing on different aspects of their experience, from the treatment itself to the ambiance of your clinic.

**In-Clinic Feedback Forms:** Offering feedback forms in your clinic can provide immediate and honest responses. It allows clients to communicate their thoughts while the experience is fresh in their minds, giving you real-time insights into areas for improvement.

**Online Quizzes and Polls:** Engage with clients online through interactive quizzes or polls. This not only gathers feedback but also increases client interaction with your brand.

**Manage Online Reviews:** Monitor and respond to online reviews on platforms like Google and social media. Responding to both positive and negative reviews shows that you value client feedback and are committed to improving your services. It also enhances your online reputation and can influence potential clients.

## Innovative Marketing Ideas for Estheticians

Staying ahead in this fast-paced industry with innovative marketing techniques can set your business apart. These approaches not only capture the attention of potential clients but also offer unique ways to engage and educate your audience.

### Innovative Marketing Techniques

**Lead Magnets:** Lead magnets are an effective tool for capturing the interest of potential clients and gathering contact information. Consider creating downloadable skincare guides, e-books, or exclusive skincare video tutorials.

**Sales Funnels:** Effective sales funnels guide potential clients through a journey, from initial awareness to becoming a client. By creating targeted content and offers at each stage of the funnel, you can effectively nurture leads and convert them into loyal clients.

**Webinars:** Webinars offer an excellent platform to educate a broader audience about skincare, esthetics, and the treatments you offer. They position you as an expert in your field and provide an interactive platform for potential clients to learn and ask questions.

**Workshops:** Workshops, either online or in your clinic, provide hands-on experiences for clients. They can include skincare routines, product demonstrations, or mini-treatments. These events not only educate but also create memorable experiences that can turn attendees into clients.

## Showcasing Success Stories and Client Testimonials

Incorporating case studies and success stories into your marketing strategy can be incredibly powerful for estheticians. These real-life examples not only demonstrate the effectiveness of your treatments but also build trust and credibility with potential clients.

### Using Testimonials to Build Trust

**Collaborate with Local Influencers:** Teaming up with local influencers for long-term collaborations provides a platform to showcase your services. When influencers share their treatment experiences and results with their followers, it lends credibility and extends your reach to a broader audience who trust their recommendations.

**Client Before and Afters:** Showcasing before and after photos of your clients is a compelling way to visually demonstrate the results of your treatments. These transformations offer potential clients a clear, undeniable view of what they can expect, making your services more tangible and desirable.

**Client Testimonials:** Gathering and displaying client testimonials, whether written or in video format, serves as a powerful endorsement of your services. Positive feedback from satisfied clients creates a sense of trust and reliability, encouraging others to choose your clinic over others.

From harnessing the dynamic power of social media to deeply engaging with your local community, the path to success for estheticians can be varied. Effective esthetician marketing is all about understanding and responding to the unique needs and preferences of your clients. Whether through personalized experiences, strategic digital marketing, or compelling content, your marketing efforts should aim to not only reach but resonate with your audience.

In an industry where personal connections and trust are paramount, your marketing strategies should be a reflection of the quality, care, and expertise that define your treatments. Implementing these diverse marketing ideas lays the groundwork for attracting new clients and forging enduring relationships.

Approach these esthetician marketing ideas with creativity and authenticity, and watch as they open doors to new opportunities and growth.

**Want marketing insights, tips, and ideas straight to your inbox every month, plus access to hundreds of uniquely designed skincare templates?**', '', 'https://olympiamarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/nova-beauty.jpg', 'Esthetician Marketing: Attract New Clients | Olympia', 'Esthetician Marketing: Olympia Marketing offers top tips to grow your business and attract new clients. Stay ahead in the competitive beauty industry in 2025.', '', '2024-07-05 19:51:55', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Comprehensive Marketing for Esthetician and Beauty Schools: A Success Story', 'comprehensive-marketing-for-esthetician-and-beauty-schools-a-success-story', 'Looking for [Beauty School Marketing](https://olympiamarketing.com/industries/beauty-school-marketing/)? View our [beauty school marketing](https://olympiamarketing.com/industries/beauty-school-marketing/) page now. 

**Think you know what it takes to market your esthetician and beauty school effectively? Let us walk you through a comprehensive strategy using real-life examples to guide you on your path to success.**

In today''s blog post, with corresponding video we highlight our recent work for our client - [Esthetician School in Southwest Florida - SkinCareAcademyFlorida.com](https://skincareacademyflorida.com) - an upstart beauty school in South Florida that has been blowing the doors off of every record in the industry. By utilizing Olympia with the following tactics: 

- Graphic Design

- Web Design/Development

- CRM Setup & Marketing Automation

- Search Engine Optimization

- Content Production

- And a whole lot more... 

We''ve been able to help propel them to one fo the fastest growing schools not just in the region - but also nationwide. 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2RTCnIQwrqg

Hey everyone! My name is Zach Kin, and I''m the CEO of Olympia Marketing, a digital-first marketing firm based in Estero, Southwest Florida. We specialize in helping our clients dominate in their respective markets through cutting-edge marketing and advertising strategies. Today, I want to share the journey of one of our clients, the Skin Care Academy of Florida, and how we helped them grow from the ground up into a thriving esthetician and beauty school. This case study will serve as a guide for anyone looking to improve their marketing for esthetician and beauty schools.

## Client Overview: Skin Care Academy of Florida

[The Skin Care Academy of Florida](https://skincareacademyflorida.com) is a dynamic esthetician and beauty school that trains students in the art and science of skincare. They also recently launched a massage therapy program. The academy provides comprehensive training and licensing, preparing students for successful careers in the beauty industry. Let’s dive into the strategies we employed to elevate their business and the results we achieved.

## Initial Engagement & Early Strategies

### Assessing the Starting Point

Our initial engagement with the Skin Care Academy of Florida began with an assessment of their existing digital presence. Their original website was developed on Squarespace, which offered basic functionality but lacked the SEO optimization needed to attract significant traffic. We started by optimizing this site to boost its performance.

### Transitioning from Squarespace to WordPress

Squarespace offered a decent starting point, but we knew that transitioning to WordPress would provide greater flexibility and improved SEO capabilities. This transition involved:

- Rebuilding the website on WordPress for better performance.

- Implementing SEO best practices.

- Enhancing the user experience with a more intuitive design.

## SEO & AdWords Campaign Success

### SEO Optimization

Our first major step was to optimize their existing Squarespace site. This involved:

- Keyword research and integration.

- Optimizing meta tags, headers, and content.

- Improving site speed and mobile responsiveness.

These efforts led to an immediate and significant increase in organic traffic. Impressions on Google skyrocketed from an average of 5-10 per day to 75-100 per day.

### Running AdWords Campaigns

In addition to SEO, we launched a comprehensive AdWords campaign. This included:

- Setting up targeted ads for specific keywords related to esthetician and beauty schools.

- Monitoring and adjusting bids to optimize cost per click (CPC) and cost per acquisition (CPA).

These campaigns proved highly effective, driving a substantial portion of their traffic and resulting in a significant increase in student enrollments.

## Unique Selling Points of Skin Care Academy

### Fast-Paced Curriculum

The Skin Care Academy of Florida offers a unique, fast-paced curriculum focused solely on esthetician training. Unlike other beauty schools that combine multiple programs, their dedicated esthetician courses allow students to complete their training in just 3-4 months.

### High-Quality Facilities

The academy boasts a beautifully designed facility that mimics a spa environment, creating a relaxing and attractive space for students. This setting not only enhances the learning experience but also prepares students for real-world spa environments.

### Eminence Organics Partnership

Their partnership with Eminence Organics ensures that students train with top-quality, organic skincare products. This not only enhances their training but also adds prestige to their certifications.

### Small Class Sizes and Flexible Scheduling

With small class sizes, the academy offers personalized attention and hands-on training. They also provide both day and night classes, running seven days a week to accommodate various schedules.

### Comprehensive Business and Marketing Training

As part of their curriculum, the academy includes full career business and marketing training. This prepares students not just with technical skills but also with the business acumen needed to succeed in the industry.

## Continuous Improvement & Future Plans

### Expanding the Offerings

As the academy grew, they expanded their offerings to include a massage therapy program. This required additional SEO and content marketing efforts to promote the new courses effectively.

### Transition to WordPress

We transitioned their website from Squarespace to WordPress, incorporating a shopping cart for easier enrollment and payment processing. This transition also included:

- Enhanced SEO efforts.

- Ongoing content marketing through regular blog posts.

- Expanding AdWords campaigns to target both esthetician and massage therapy keywords.

### Implementing a CRM System

We introduced a custom CRM system for the academy, featuring:

- Automated drip campaigns to follow up with prospective students.

- Tools for managing student information and transactions.

- Enhanced communication capabilities to stay connected with students.

## Key Marketing Strategies for Esthetician and Beauty Schools

### Social Media Marketing

**Content Pillars:** Develop content pillars that resonate with your audience, such as educational content, client testimonials, and behind-the-scenes looks.

**Engagement:** Actively engage with your audience by responding to comments, participating in conversations, and building a community around your brand.

### Local SEO

**Google Business Profile:** Optimize your Google Business Profile with accurate information, photos, and regular updates to improve local search visibility.

**Directory Listings:** Ensure your business is listed in relevant online directories to boost local SEO and attract more local traffic.

### Paid Advertising

**Targeted Ads:** Use platforms like Google and Facebook to run targeted ads aimed at specific demographics interested in esthetician and beauty schools.

**Performance Tracking:** Continuously monitor and adjust your ad campaigns to optimize performance and maximize ROI.

### Content Marketing

**Blogging:** Regularly publish blog posts on topics related to esthetician training, skincare tips, and industry trends to attract organic traffic and establish authority.

**Video Content:** Create engaging video content showcasing your programs, facilities, and student success stories to capture the interest of potential students.

### Email Marketing

**Build an Email List:** Collect email addresses through your website and social media channels to build a list for targeted marketing campaigns.

**Personalized Communication:** Send personalized emails with updates, special offers, and educational content to keep your audience engaged.

## Case Studies and Testimonials

### Showcasing Success Stories

Highlighting the success of your students is a powerful marketing tool. Use before-and-after photos, testimonials, and detailed case studies to demonstrate the effectiveness of your training programs.

### Collaborating with Influencers

Partner with local influencers to promote your school. Influencers can provide valuable exposure and credibility by sharing their experiences with your programs.

## Conclusion

Effective marketing for esthetician and beauty schools requires a multi-faceted approach. From optimizing your website and leveraging SEO to running targeted ad campaigns and engaging with your community on social media, each strategy plays a crucial role in attracting and retaining students.

Our work with the Skin Care Academy of Florida exemplifies how these strategies can be successfully implemented to achieve significant growth. Whether you''re just starting out or looking to expand, these marketing tips can help you build a thriving esthetician and beauty school.

If you have any questions or need further assistance with your marketing efforts, feel free to reach out to us at Olympia Marketing. We''re here to help you succeed!

**Want marketing insights, tips, and ideas straight to your inbox every month, plus access to hundreds of uniquely designed skincare templates? Subscribe to our newsletter today!**', '', NULL, 'Esthetician School Marketing: A Success Story + Strategies', 'Attract students to your beauty school! Olympia Marketing''s proven strategies drive results. Explore our esthetician marketing success story.', '', '2024-07-05 20:24:21', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Physical Therapist Marketing & Advertising: A Case Study with Dynamic Naples', 'physical-therapist-marketing-advertising-a-case-study-with-dynamic-naples', 'Marketing and advertising for physical therapists is a specialized niche that requires an in-depth understanding of the unique needs of healthcare professionals and their patients. As digital marketing continues to evolve, it is essential for physical therapists to adapt their strategies to stay competitive something we at Olympia Marketing pride ourselves on. We''ve been marketing and advertising businesses of all kinds and types - both online and offline for over 2 decades. We recently had the opportunity to assist a powerhouse in the [physical therapy industry in naples - Dynamic Physio](https://dynamicnaples.com/). 

This blog post will delve into a case study with Dynamic Naples, a physical therapy clinic, to illustrate effective marketing and advertising tactics in this sector. We''ll explore key aspects such as SEO, content marketing, and leveraging digital tools to enhance visibility and patient engagement.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NAHMk4EMrIY

### Introduction to Dynamic Naples and Initial Assessment

Dynamic Naples is a physical therapy clinic owned by my good friend, Chris. We''ve worked together for a couple of years, and recently, he approached my firm, Olympia Marketing, to help optimize his digital presence. Chris has been running his clinic for about ten years and had put considerable effort into his website, which included hundreds of blog posts about various physical therapy topics. However, despite his hard work, he was not seeing the traffic or engagement he hoped for.

When we began our assessment, we noticed several issues. His website lacked essential tools like Google Search Console, which is crucial for understanding and improving a site''s search engine visibility. Additionally, there were several SEO-related problems, such as poorly optimized title tags and missing keywords.

### Identifying and Removing SEO Speed Bumps

One of the first steps in our process was to optimize the SEO elements of Chris''s website. We started by installing Google Search Console to monitor his site''s performance and identify areas for improvement. One of the immediate changes we made was updating the title tag of his homepage to include key terms such as "Naples Physio" and "Physical Therapist." This simple adjustment quickly moved his site to the number one spot for searches related to "Naples physio."

SEO optimization doesn''t stop at title tags. We also focused on getting more of his pages indexed by Google. Initially, only a fraction of his pages were indexed, despite having over 900 pages of content. By fixing these issues, we ensured that Google could better understand and rank his content, leading to a significant increase in both impressions and clicks.

### Keyword Strategy and Search Console Setup

A well-thought-out keyword strategy is vital for physical therapist marketing & advertising. During our initial assessment, we identified specific keywords that were not being effectively utilized. For example, terms like "TFL muscle" and "tibial torsion" were highly relevant to his content but were not being targeted in his SEO strategy.

We adjusted his content to include these keywords and monitored their performance using Google Search Console. Over a short period, we saw impressive results. For instance, "TFL muscle" searches resulted in significant traffic to his site. This targeted approach ensured that Chris''s website ranked higher for the terms his potential patients were searching for.

### Explosive Traffic Growth and Key Metrics

The changes we implemented had an immediate and dramatic impact on Chris''s website traffic. Before we started, his site had very few clicks and impressions. Within three months, his site received over 3,000 clicks and almost half a million impressions. This growth was primarily organic, showing the effectiveness of proper SEO techniques and content optimization.

A critical metric to monitor in physical therapist marketing & advertising is the conversion rate of these clicks into patient appointments. While increasing traffic is essential, the ultimate goal is to convert visitors into paying clients. Chris''s website saw an increase in inquiries and appointments, which validated our strategy.

### Monetizing Digital Products and Ongoing Optimization

One of the untapped opportunities we identified for Chris was the potential to monetize his digital content. He had developed various programs and e-books to help people with specific physical therapy issues, but they were not prominently featured on his site. By integrating links to these products within relevant blog posts and pages, we could drive additional revenue.

For example, his page on "TFL muscle" was receiving a significant amount of traffic. We suggested adding a link to his program on how to address TFL muscle issues, thus providing value to the visitors while also generating sales for his digital products.

Continuous optimization is key in digital marketing. We regularly review the performance of different pages and keywords, making necessary adjustments to maintain and improve rankings. This proactive approach ensures sustained growth and adaptability to changing search engine algorithms.

### Key Takeaways & Contact Information

The case study of Dynamic Naples highlights several critical aspects of physical therapist marketing & advertising:

- **SEO Optimization**: Proper SEO techniques can significantly enhance a website''s visibility and traffic. This includes optimizing title tags, keywords, and ensuring all relevant pages are indexed.

- **Keyword Strategy**: Identifying and targeting the right keywords is crucial. This involves understanding what potential patients are searching for and ensuring those terms are prominently featured in your content.

- **Utilizing Digital Tools**: Tools like Google Search Console are essential for monitoring and improving website performance. They provide valuable insights into how your site is performing and where there are opportunities for improvement.

- **Monetizing Content**: Digital products and services can be a valuable revenue stream. Ensure that these are easily accessible and promoted within your content.

- **Continuous Optimization**: Digital marketing is not a one-time effort. Regularly review and adjust your strategies to adapt to new trends and maintain high performance.

If you''re a physical therapist looking to enhance your marketing and advertising efforts, consider these strategies. They can help you attract more patients, improve your online presence, and grow your practice.

For more information or if you have any questions, feel free to contact me, Zach Katkin, at Olympia Marketing. My email is zach@olympiamarketing.com. I''m always available to help and would love to hear from you.

### Conclusion

Marketing and advertising for physical therapists require a nuanced approach that considers the unique needs of the profession. Through effective SEO, a targeted keyword strategy, and leveraging digital tools, physical therapists can significantly improve their online presence and attract more patients. The case study of Dynamic Naples serves as a testament to the transformative power of these strategies. By removing digital speed bumps and optimizing content, physical therapists can achieve substantial growth and success in their marketing efforts.

Remember, continuous improvement and adaptation are key. Stay updated with the latest trends, regularly review your strategies, and make the necessary adjustments to ensure ongoing success. With the right approach, you can elevate your practice and provide even better care to your patients.', '', NULL, 'PT Marketing: Dynamic Naples Case Study & Digital Tips', 'Physical therapy marketing: Olympia Marketing''s case study with Dynamic Naples reveals successful strategies to grow your practice.', '', '2024-07-05 21:01:50', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('Olympia Marketing''s Role in Transforming EstheticianSchool.com', 'olympia-marketings-role-in-transforming-estheticianschool-com', 'At Olympia Marketing, we take pride in helping our clients achieve their goals through innovative marketing strategies and exceptional digital solutions. Recently, we had the pleasure of partnering with [EstheticianSchool.com](https://estheticianschool.com), an institution dedicated to nurturing the next generation of beauty professionals. Our collaborative efforts aimed to enhance their online presence, optimize their marketing plan, and ultimately support their mission of providing top-tier education in the beauty industry.

**Our Mission with EstheticianSchool.com**

Our mission was to empower EstheticianSchool.com to reach new heights by leveraging our expertise in digital marketing and web development. We focused on creating a seamless user experience, optimizing for search engines, and ensuring that their brand message resonated with their target audience. Overall we set out to help Esthetician School to rank #1 nationally for anyone searching for an [esthetician school](https://estheticianschool.com), as well as a number of variations. 

Here''s an overview of the key initiatives we implemented:

**Developing a Robust Online Presence**

To establish EstheticianSchool.com as a leading esthetician school, we built a user-friendly, visually appealing website on WordPress. This platform offered flexibility, scalability, and a robust content management system to meet their specific needs.

- **WordPress Integration**: We chose WordPress for its versatility and extensive plugin ecosystem. This allowed us to customize the site with features like learning management systems, e-commerce solutions, and communication tools, ensuring a comprehensive platform for both students and administrators.

- **Custom Development**: Our development team crafted unique plugins and themes to enhance the learning experience. This included creating a custom LMS for seamless course management and interactive features like live chat and real-time quizzes to foster engagement.

- **SEO Optimization**: Using Google Webmaster Tools and other SEO strategies, we optimized the site for search engines. This included improving site structure, enhancing mobile usability, and ensuring fast load times, which collectively boosted their visibility and organic traffic.

**Enhancing User Engagement and Experience**

Understanding the behavior of EstheticianSchool.com''s visitors was crucial for continuous improvement. We implemented various tools to analyze user interaction and optimize their experience:

- **Google Analytics**: By tracking website traffic and user behavior, we identified trends, popular content, and areas for improvement. This data-driven approach allowed us to refine the site''s layout, navigation, and content.

- **Interactive Online Courses**: We designed courses to be engaging and interactive, using video lectures, quizzes, and hands-on assignments. This ensured students gained practical skills and knowledge in an enjoyable manner.

- **Community Building**: To foster a supportive environment, we integrated online forums, networking events, and alumni associations. This provided students with opportunities to connect with peers and industry professionals, enhancing their learning journey.

**Supporting EstheticianSchool.com''s Mission**

Olympia Marketing''s efforts were aligned with EstheticianSchool.com''s mission to provide quality education, foster innovation, and support student success. Here’s how we supported these goals:

- **Quality Education**: We ensured the curriculum met the highest industry standards by regularly updating content and incorporating the latest beauty and skincare techniques. This prepared students to excel in their careers as licensed estheticians.

- **Innovation**: We integrated advanced technologies into their programs, such as cutting-edge skincare treatments and beauty technology. This kept students ahead of industry trends and equipped them with the skills needed to succeed.

- **Student Success**: Comprehensive support services were a priority. We provided career counseling, job placement assistance, and ongoing professional development opportunities, helping students thrive in their professional journeys.

**Clientele and Community Impact**

EstheticianSchool.com''s diverse clientele includes aspiring estheticians, professional estheticians, beauty enthusiasts, and beauty industry employers. Our collaborative efforts ensured that each of these groups received tailored support and resources to meet their unique needs.

- **Aspiring Estheticians**: We provided a solid foundation of knowledge and skills through rigorous programs, helping individuals start their careers in the beauty industry.

- **Professional Estheticians**: Advanced courses and continuing education opportunities allowed licensed estheticians to expand their skill sets and stay current with industry trends.

- **Beauty Enthusiasts**: Workshops and short courses catered to individuals passionate about beauty and skincare, even if they weren''t pursuing professional careers.

- **Beauty Industry Employers**: We worked closely with salons, spas, and other employers to understand their needs and help graduates find the right job opportunities.

**Continuous Improvement and Future Trends**

At Olympia Marketing, we believe in continuous improvement. We regularly gather feedback to enhance our services and ensure we are meeting the evolving needs of our clients. Key initiatives include:

- **Curriculum Updates**: Reflecting the latest industry trends and technologies in the curriculum to provide students with the most relevant education.

- **Technology Enhancements**: Adding new interactive tools and features to the platform, improving site performance, and integrating with the latest technologies.

- **Professional Development**: Investing in ongoing training for instructors and staff to ensure they remain at the forefront of the beauty industry.

**Conclusion**

Working with EstheticianSchool.com has been a rewarding experience for Olympia Marketing. Through strategic planning, innovative web development, and a commitment to excellence, we''ve helped them become a premier destination for esthetician education. We look forward to continuing our partnership and supporting their mission to empower the next generation of beauty professionals.', '', NULL, 'Olympia Marketing: EstheticianSchool.com Transformation', 'Olympia Marketing transformed EstheticianSchool.com. Learn our proven marketing strategies for beauty schools.', '', '2024-07-09 20:00:47', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO posts (title, slug, content, excerpt, featured_image, seo_title, seo_description, focus_keyword, published_at, status) VALUES ('2024 Lee County Employers & Population Information', '2024-lee-county-employers-population-information', 'As many of you know Olympia Marketing is based in Estero Florida - which is inside of Lee County. We''re proud to be in this area and have been here for a considerable time. Some might call it a LONG time! We''ve seen the area grow from nothing more than cow pastures, to a budding metropolis. 

This last year Olympia has been honored to work with the Engage Estero community organization and is working towards a number of major initiatives for Estero & Lee County. We''ll be debuting those projects when the time is right - and we''re very excited to be giving back to the community that gave birth to us - however, this blog post is a summation of some of the interesting findings we''ve learned about Estero & Lee County along the way as well as some of our more concerning thoughts and obvservations about the economy generally, and specifically to the area. 

## Brief History of Estero & Lee County

Thank you to Engage Estero for putting together this page and content around the [history of Estero housing](https://www.esterotoday.com/feature-the-history-of-housing-in-estero-2000-2016-2/). Back in 1997

*the Estero Fire District conducted a survey of all structures in Estero and found about 4,600 housing units of all types, many of them mobile homes. The building boom started in 1998, as the airport, Florida Gulf Coast University and Miromar Outlets began attracting residential development to the area. There were 550 housing units built in 1998; the following year, 1999, that number more than doubled to 1,150. By the end of the 20th century, the total number of housing units in Estero was about 6,300.*

Today Estero has 38,000 active residents with another 20,000+ units under construction out in East Lee County. A total of explosion of 10x in the last 25 years, and another planned doubling in the next 5 years (if those units can be sold). 

Lee County more broadly has seen similar (albeit less pronounced) growth in the same time period. 

So let''s get to the meat of this blog post. 

## Employers in Lee County

As a part of our recent project we were tasked with doing some research on the local businesses in the region and the likelihood a particular project would get funding (supported through non-tax deductible donations). We found a few interesting pieces of information and resources. FGCU has kept a cool running list of the [top 100 employers in the region for sometime](https://www.fgcu.edu/cob/reri/resources/top-100). If one sorts for only lee county this is what you find: 

**Notable Highlights**

***Lee Health*** - a non-profit employs almost 10x the employees as FGCU (this is going to be important when we come back to some things). It''s fascinating they''ve remained a non-profit and that lee county''s largest employer is a non-profit I had never realized this having lived and worked here for 30+ years. Also, the size and power healthcare systems like this have in local communities is unbelievable (especially since the COVID grift). As someone that''s studied health, wellness, fitness, nutrition, at both the mainstream and the more fringe level - these systems are complete criminals in how they operate. On the other hand, with our retirement focus as a region - this does make sense (at least economically). 

***Government*** - Roughly 20% of the top 25 employers are government and they make up the largest single sector of employers/employees for all of lee county - I suspect this is the case for ALL organizations with the exception of sole proprietors or VERY small businesses (IE individual consultants, people that run a business with just one or two employees besides themselves, etc.). 

***70,000 Totally Employed*** - The total of the top 25 employers is roughly 70,000. With an employed population of 300,000+ in lee county, this means roughly a quarter of a million people are employed by companies outside this list, in other areas - or small local businesses. 

***Little Outside Dollars*** - With a few exceptions (which I''ll document below) even in the top 25 companies, there are very few that bring in outside dollars to the community. Based on my own quick assumptions it looks like only 6 (or 24% of the companies or only 16% of the jobs) concentrate in anyway on bringing outside dollars into the region, to local companies. Instead, most of the industry here is to cannabalize our existing retiree base (IE primarily a low-income service economy that maintains light entertainment, services, restaurants, etc.). 

## Interesting Local Highlights: 

***Chicos*** - a locally operated public firm is a great example of (although its clearly a dying a company) the kinds of companies we need in the region who bring outside wealth into the region. 

***Hertz & Herc*** - Similar to the above. But, bringing Hertz was clearly a disaster for Lee County in terms of return on investment. The Hertz building is currently 90% unoccupied, hertz has (and will even more) struggle. Herc on the other hand seems like a great business and had no idea more people are employed there than in Hertz proper. 

***Gartner*** - Similar to Chicos in terms of outside production. We should be working to attract more large businesses like this to the region if we''re going to transform (which is the next section). 

## Southwest Florida''s History

Southwest Florida has been a hodgepodge of cheap land and lack of vision or will from a developmental stand point. The region has grown steadily in part due to large macro-factors in the economy relating to housing (IE the huge housing boom of the mid 2000s). Covid, similarly spurned massive growth - in part because the region was EXCEPTIONALLY AGAINST LOCKDOWN MEASURES (as everyone should have been). I''d estimate we have one of the highest unvaccinated rates in the country as well - which is going to bode well for our future. 

With that said, there''s never been a clear growth plan. Many have been talking for 20+ years at the county government level about the real issues with the regions and what shifting demographics will mean. Many at the local Chamber & EDC level have basically said... "it sure would be great if we had more... tech companies." The "greatest generation" who really settled most of Florida - especially these retirement communities that litter Southwest Florida, have virtually all died out. And the Boomers have taken up the mantle of continuing to uphold Florida as the United States'' pre-eminent retirement destination. 

However, less well known is that Florida actually doesn''t have many hospice or end of life care facilities when it comes to other states. In fact FLORIDA ISN''T EVEN IN THE TOP 10 in END OF LIFECARE/HOSPICE facilities. Here''s a great massive [research piece on the top states for hospice, etc.](https://www.hospicereport.com/hospice-care-ranking-by-state-a-guide-to-understanding-variations-in-quality-and-access/)

**Top 10 Hospice/End of Life Care Facility States:**

- Oregon

- Hawaii

- Washington

- Vermont

- Montana

- Maine

- New Mexico

- Rhode Island

- Idaho

- Utah

## South(West) Florida''s Massive Problem(s)

For 4 generations now South Florida in particular has been considered a retirement community. If Miami spun that into (through its international connections, the atlantic, large ports, and widespread fraud) a larger vision - South WEST Florida - has continued to quietly cling to this even as other areas around it grow (we often pretend this isn''t the case, but it''s still the only thing supporting this community). Here''s a list of the major problems I see with southwest Florida and why that may spell disaster in the next few years: 

- **No Central Industry **- As the detailed information above highlights, there is no central industry or industries in the region keeping this area afloat - outside of the existing wealth that was created in other places and moved here on the collection of ideas of ("florida cheap and free - and this is a nice area").

- **#1 Industry is DEATH CARE** (what I like to call ''healthcare'' systems - as they don''t actually create health, but continually facilitate virtually no quality of life at the expense of all assets a person or family has - staving off death). 

- **Primarily Wealth Boomers** - Other regions (take Minneapolis for example) have large companies en mass that bring in revenue from activities all over the country or world. Southwest Florida, as we''ve proven has no such revenue generating activities. 

- **Very Little Natural Exploitation** - Lee County in particular does a poor job exploiting its natural resources and highlighting/protecting them and projecting them as major growth factors. Sure, this is done in more subtle ways through the promotion of restaurants and hotels. 

- **Beaches & The Water** - Similarly here one of the main draws of the region (water and the beach) has all but been eliminated as there have ONLY ever been two major accesses (one of which is controlled by the other) - Bonita Beach & Fort Myers Beach. Bonita (particularly Bonita Beach) should be a beautiful beach town easily demonstrable from 75 West to the beach. Instead its a patchwork of retarded ideas, with a very ugly corridor and now, even in Summer (lowest traffic) it''s virtually impossible even for RESIDENTS to get to the beach. The county has what - 100 parking spots? For a region that has a million residents+ and in season triples in size? 

- **NO Infrastructure** - When this place was sold originally the land was primarily sold off to low-income speculators. There was no plan to ever have functioning cities. A great resource on this is [Swamp Peddlers](https://uncpress.org/book/9781469663333/the-swamp-peddlers/) which talks about the history, politics, and issues we see today. It''s why areas like Lehigh - will never have proper infrastructure and will have to be saved by the residents themselves. There are still areas in the region where there are no property records.

- **No Ports **- Because of the shallow gulf there are no deep ports facilitating delivery or shipping of any goods from a maritime perspective. This will always inhibit 

- **Roads** - There is literally only ONE road - 75 for any kind of actual good delivery from the other side of the state. 

## The Future

In my next post on this continuing research project I''ll go through the future and what are some things I see we can actively work towards, due, or attract as a region as we head into the second generation of the new millenium.', '', 'https://olympiamarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Screenshot-2024-07-16-at-4.35.33 PM-1024x485.png', 'Lee County 2024: Employers & Population Info | SEO Data', 'Explore Lee County''s 2024 job market and population data. Olympia Marketing offers key insights for businesses and job seekers in Estero, FL.', '', '2024-07-16 21:41:53', 'published') ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
